metadata.name: de|growth:generations #47
metadata.description:
Materials tend to take particular forms due to their physical properties, technological necessities or natural limitations. However, what rules should a simulated environment follow when no physical constraints are inherent to the digital environment?

This project continues the exploration of shaping digital matter that I began on hicetnunc in 2021. Each token creates an image of a unique sculpture generated with a custom growth/degrowth algorithm. The image is rendered with a tailored raytracing script.

---
Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones for the 800x800px image.

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the resolution from preview quality to a print of approx. 30x30cm. There may be minor differences in tone or contrast for different resolutions.

In live mode:
Click PNG to save the rendered image.
Click STL to download the digital model to view on your computer or 3d print at home [experimental]

metadata.name: Breeding Grounds #73
metadata.description:
Social Networks.
Molecular Clouds.
Neuronal Circuitries.
Quantum Mechanical Structures.

Blurring Boundaries.
Infinite Self-Similarities.

Total.
Mess.

Perfect.
Order.

/////
Each element (besides the painting ground textures) is based on the underlying subdivided grid which is sometimes exposed like some kind of preliminary drawing.

Note on the split:
After seeing some of the outputs, Sermin had a dream about “Breeding Grounds” and I decided to incorporate events and feelings from her dream into the project. That's how the names of the color palettes came about. Thank you for naming them, Sermin!

Press 's' to save a .png with the current resolution (2000x3000).
If you want a file with higher resolution and/or without the “Painting Ground Textures” for printing please contact me via Twitter or Discord. 

/////
Created with p5.js

Twitter: @serminmin / @pxlshrd

metadata.name: "The blood coagulates.” -Randoms Performs. #17
metadata.description:
"It is the part of the body that wants to flee and is frustrated by the limits of the skin, the body in movement keeps the dance contained as a means of survival but also so that we do not escape from ourselves. A puddle of blood on the floor is a waste, the mark of a bruise is the witness of the frustration and violence that the movement entails. "

This is a collab with Gregorio Nash (@gregorionash).

Technical Data :
Five movements that mix infinitely, each combination makes for a unique performance. It also has an "Old Vintage" shader that gives an old and worn feeling. The movements were created from a sensoperceptive experimentation through the body kinesphere, decanting a saying of the body understanding the sensations from an active role.

Variations :
- 5 performances.
- Infinite palette color possibilities
- Shader "Old Vintage".

thanks to Julian Puppo (@jpupper), for helping us with the construction of the code and the shaders.
thanks to Javier Meseguer (jmpep) for shader “old vintage”.

metadata.name: Touch me #12
metadata.description:
This generative work shows an unstable parametric geometry. The instability is activated only after a first interaction (hence the title invitation).
Through different passages and different states of complexity, the model seems to seek its own balance, but without ever reaching it.
